    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-26T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="393"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/936: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-26T18:00:00+07:00"
                            >June 26, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 27—3:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1031. For Secretary [of] Treasury only from Adler: TF–135. Re your 797, June 23.
                    Informally communicated your views to Dr. Kung yesterday. He indicated that he
                    would ask for revision of 1941 Agreement. [Adler.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
